
MFA: multi-factor authentication


- Phone MFA (call or SMS)
- TOTP: Time-based One Time Password - life google authenticator
- Push-Based MFA: app gets authentication request that user accept or denied
  - cons: fatigue attack (malicious multiple requests)
- Webauthn: hardware keys and TLS + Publick Keys
  - Idp  -(challenge for User)-> Browser -(please verify challenge)-> Authenticator (app, hw) -(sign Challenge using PK)-> Browser -(send Signature using PK)->  IdP
  - Authenticator talks directly to Browser

Term:
IdP: Identity Provider.
PK: Public Key
TLS: Transport Layer Security
SK: Secret Key
